    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that seems kind of wishy-washy lol. if you look at the math, you can't just keep printing money for social programs without eventually hitting a wall where the debt interest alone destroys the budget. isn't it basically true that prioritizing social spending over debt reduction is just short-sighted and economically unsound in the long run?",
